<dl id="n40042c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40042c">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40042c"> 42(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Satan / (adversary / Zaravas</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The conception of Satan (Heb. <font color="green">[=]</font> the adversary, Gr. &Sigma;&alpha;&tau;&alpha;&upsilon;&#x1F00;&sigma;, or &Sigma;&alpha;&tau;&upsilon;, 2 Cor. xii. 7)belongs to the post-exilic period of Hebrew development, and probably shows traces of the influence of Persian on Jewish thought, ,but it has also its roots in much older beliefs. <small> &ldquo;DEVIL&rdquo; <a name="EBDV" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EBDV"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) VIII 121</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
